06/11/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Milan Bandic, mayor of Zagreb, announced on Thursday (November 5th) that he will run for president next month.
Bandic, 54, a co-founder of the main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP), says he'll run as an independent.
Immediately after he announced that, the SDP said it suspended his membership in the party.
The SDP's candidate in the December 27th presidential race is Ivo Josipovic.
(HRT, Index, Jutarnji list, Vecernji List, Javno - 05/11/09)
